content:
@Elyse<br>
<br>
I think that me being apologetic is not being scummy. It's just that since this is my first game I feel a little guilty because I feel like I was being influenced a little too quickly at the beginning of the game and posting too quick before thinking out my posts and I just don't want to annoy people so I'm trying to think it out a little more before I comment. That's why I also mentioned that for now I want to hear more comments before I take a vote.

@Mirhawk, why were you pushing Josh B to answer Slandaar's question but you wouldn't ask Slandaar to answer Josh B's? They both aren't about you. Both try to force players to give opinons on the gamestate. Yet, only one is your question.<br>
<br>
That in "Titusese" is an associative tell. You associate the Slandaar question as your question. You have an innate liking of Slandaar. The only question is whether you hastily gave him a townread too early or are you buddies with him?<br>
<br>
@Josh B... you need to answer that question, just as Slandaar needs to give his opinion.

@TSO<br>
What are your thoughts on Elise?<br>
<br>
@Titus<br>
Have you played against Slandaar when he was town?

@Bacde, no I am not. I am trying to understand you but all you're doing is putting out nonsense, which is not normal you. You're also more defensive. I'm paranoid, sure. I'm not trying to paint you as scummy. I want Slandaar dead.<br>
<br>
@Mirhawk, yes. See Death's Diner, completed Large Theme.

@Bacde<br>
You know what to be honest I was about 6 to 7 pages behind so I kinda skimmed through quickly to try and get the gist of it so I could make a comment. I must have missed some of your points. <br>
<br>
@Reinoe<br>
Why do you feel that Titus is town?

@Elyse, I wasn't referring to Bacde's logic on Pacman. But to further that point.. what logic? Do you have daychat with Bacde? (The reason for this question will become obvious after Elyse answers.) I was referring to the whole "unintentionally manipulative" debate. That is relevant because it places Wake in obvtown status.<br>
<br>
@Slandaar, you have refused to post opinions for days. By the time I'm begging for opinions, a player almost certainly has gone days without posting.<br>
<br>
@Wake, use your annihilator beam. Sort me. Have me do jumping chicken dances. I don't care. You're town.

@Wake, defense attorneys are not obsfuscators...that's the prosecution, which more fits Bacde's behavior. Bacde is trying to push through a wagon on Josh B and stopping any wagon that may lead elsewhere.<br>
<br>
I got bigger issues with Slandaar but consider the wagons tied.

@Elise, Mini 1474: Desperado's revenge... everyone was a bag of lurksacks in it, so much the mod commented post game.<br>
<br>
@Bacde, I don't promise to sheep ever. You oughta know that by now. Titus doesn't sheep. If you present good cases, I will follow. The likelihood of that occurring goes up in the astronomical event Slandaar is town.<br>
<br>
@Josh B, No. You are listening to the scums. Stop it. You had your vote on scum, now you don't. This makes me want to cry.

@Elyse, using "we" when referring to town as a townslip. Oh good grief. Oh and nice fenceshit on me.<br>
<br>
@JoshB, a couple of things. First, if you're a major wagon that is not scum, scum won't be NKing you. There's literally no reason to do something so derpy as voting a townread. Your post in that indicated you were playing with much more of a survival mindset. Stop. Assume you will not live to see Day 2. Play that way. Also, you are assuming many things... first, scum don't buddy each other. I tend to do that a lot as scum. Second, you're assuming TSO's comments have some bearing on Slandaar telling the truth (how?)<br>
<br>
It's also a big rule for both town and scum to kiss the vig's ass if you believe that he's a vig.<br>
<br>
@All, we have allegedly three PRs in a 13 player game. That should be the cap with normal balancing. If anyone is a PR (don't claim what) you should probably speak up at this point.<br>
<br>
Skot/chaos/me/Elyse/Pacman/TYR (where is that dude?)/reinoe/Mirhawk/Wake/TSO is the lynch pool unless someone else says PR. If your vote isn't in there, move it.<br>
<br>
@SKOT/TSO -- Talk to other people. Your shitfest is getting nowhere and it's not revealing alignment for anyone.

Wake is that type of player though. I've played a fair amount with him, and he's mostly been town. I've scumread him for the same reasons you (Josh and Reinoe) are. Look at the other votes on Wake. They literally suck.<br>
<br>
@Reinoe, then can we vote the scumreads we agree on and save Wake for later?

@Wake, try it sure. Do what you think is best. You don't need my permission to do anything.<br>
<br>
@Elyse, your insistance that I couldn't have a townread on Reinoe put you on my radar initially. Then, except for Wake, you've been pushing everything in reverse of what I believe is the right response. Your play, on a gut level, also harkens back to that one game where you and Aphix were scumbuddies.

@Slandaar - Objection: Vague...what is the comparison?<br>
<br>
Also I did link to scum you. Anyone could see your meta.

reinoe, stop. put your vote back on Elyse. Elyse is the one they don't want lynched and are desperate.<br>
<br>
@slandaar, I'm not reinventing the wheel when reinoe already did answer your question about where I pursued patterns. It was poor form to garcia me though.

@Pacman<br>
<a href="http://forum.mafiascum.net/viewtopic.php?f=53&amp;t=29925" class="postlink">http://forum.mafiascum.net/viewtopic.php?f=53&amp;t=29925</a><br>
This is the game Titus linked me to.

@Elyse<br>
For me as I went through and re-looked through the posts about you especially about the vote count reset, I at first was leaning towards Titus or Slandaar but had my suspicions about you. But with Slandaar's recent case and Titus' comments as well my suspicions about you rose. So maybe it was not specifically "new" evidence against you, but instead it was more because of the lack of evidence imo of the others I had suspicions about. Also, I feel that if you end up not being scum, your lynch would be a good way to hunt down scum because then we can start hunting the people who pushed for your lynch more thoroughly.<br>
If you need me to I will list all the posts that changed my mind if this was not enough information

@MOD the thread still says it's night.<br>
<br>
Wake, please give us the results of Sharpest's investigations so far.
